The paper introduces a new data structure called the choice dictionary and studies additional space-efficient data structures for subsets of $\{1,\ldots,n\}$. These topics are closely related to data structures and algorithms, which are covered in the computer science sub-categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also mentions graph and combinatorial problems, which fall under the sub-categories cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS and cs.CC, followed by cs.DM, cs.CG, and cs.LG.
